No captive insurer shall voluntarily take any of the following material actions without providing the commissioner at least thirty (30) days' prior written notice and receiving the commissionerâ€™s approval of the action within the thirty (30) day period:
The dissolution of the captive insurer;
Any sale, exchange, lease, mortgage, assignment, pledge, or other transfer of, or granting of a security interest in, all or substantially all of the assets of the captive insurer;
Any incurrence of material indebtedness by the captive insurer;
Any making of a material loan or other material extension of credit by the captive insurer;
Any payment or distribution that materially reduces capital and surplus;
Any merger or consolidation to which the captive insurer is a constituent party;
Any conversion of the captive insurer to another business form;
Any transfer to or domestication in any jurisdiction by the captive insurer; or
Any material amendment of the organizational documents of the captive insurer, including changes in the officers, directors, owners, captive manager, actuary, or auditor.
